<http://dx.doi.org/10.1002/ajp.22631>
    bibo:endPage "15" ;
    bibo:journal "American Journal of Primatology" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "79" ;
    dc:creator "Peng-Fei Fan; Kai He; Xing Chen; Alejandra Ortiz; Bin Zhang; Chao Zhao; Yun-Qiao; Hai-Bo Zhang; Clare Kimock; Wen-Zhi Wang; Colin Groves; Samuel T. Turvey; Christian Roos; Kristofer M. Helgen; Kristofer M. Helgen; Xue-Long Jiang" ;
    dc:date "2017" ;
    dc:title "Description of a new species of Hoolock gibbon (Primates: Hylobatidae) based on integrative taxonomy" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.400645>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.400650>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.400647>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.400648>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.400649>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.400644> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.400645>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3 A hoolock specimen from Homushu Pass, Mt. Gaoligong (AMNH M- 43068, top row) and the holotype of H. leuconedys (NHM ZD. 1950.391, bottom row), showing (left to right) eye brows and suborbital area, beard, and genital tuft" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/400645/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.400650>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8 A juvenile male of H. tianxing from Mt. Gaoligong jumping across trees. Photo taken by Lei Dong" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/400650/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.400647>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5 Lower p 4 of different hoolock species and geographic populations" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/400647/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.400648>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6 Bayesian tree of various catarrhines estimated using complete mitochondrial genome sequence data. Branch lengths represent time. Node bars indicate the 95 % CI for the clade age. Unless specified, all interspecific relationships are strongly supported (PP = 1.0). PPs lower than 1.0 are shown in gray. Numbers above the nodes indicate Bayesian posterior probabilities, numbers below the nodes refer to median ages" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/400648/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.400649>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7 Mitochondrial gene tree for hoolocks, showing two major clades within Hoolock leuconedys sensu lato. Specimens shaded in gray were originally identified as H. hoolock. Node numbers indicate Bayesian posterior probabilities. Branch lengths represent substitutions / site" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/400649/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.400644>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2 Photos of male (top row) and female (bottom row) hoolocks from different taxa and geographic populations. Photos of H. h. hoolock and H. h. mishmiensis are from Choudhury (2013)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/400644/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

